  <div class="page-manifesto__body-wrap">

    <h2 class="page-manifesto__chapter-label">Lost (Before)</h2>
    <div class="page-manifesto__body">
      <p>They move through life like ghosts, familiar routines on repeat. Smiling when expected, working past exhaustion, numbing themselves with endless scrolling. Success on paper, emptiness within. Their apartment feels both too small and too big, filled with things that were supposed to bring joy, now collecting dust.</p>
      <p>At 30, the questions start coming. Heavy, persistent. Who am I beneath these carefully curated posts? Why does every achievement feel hollow? They chase self-help books, entrepreneurship podcasts, wellness retreats, searching for answers in external voices while their own voice grows quieter.</p>
      <p>Time feels like sand slipping through fingers. Each birthday brings more pressure, more expectations to meet, more facades to maintain. They see their friends posting highlights, wondering if they're the only ones feeling lost in this hyper-connected world.</p>
      <p>Fear whispers constantly. Fear of being left behind. Fear of being truly seen. Fear of admitting that maybe, just maybe, this isn't the life they're meant to live.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="page-manifesto__chapter-label">Found (After)</h2>
    <div class="page-manifesto__body">
      <p>They walk through life awake now, feet planted firmly in each moment. The same streets look different, not because they've changed, but because the eyes seeing them have.</p>
      <p>Emotions come like weather, sometimes storms, sometimes gentle rain. They've learned to sit with them all, no longer running to chocolate or Netflix when things get heavy. There's a strange comfort in this discomfort, a freedom in letting feelings flow without judgment.</p>
      <p>The mirror reflects back someone who's learning to say "I got you" to themselves. Someone who wears their cap not as a shield, but as a daily reminder of choosing curiosity over fear, presence over escape.</p>
      <p>Their Instagram still shows highlights, but now there's raw truth in the captions. Late-night conversations with friends dive deep, no topic too vulnerable, no emotion too messy. They've found their people, not just connections, but true witnesses to their journey.</p>
      <p>Success takes on a new meaning. It lives in small moments, in choosing sustainability over convenience, in pursuing passion projects without guarantees, in saying no when they mean no. They're building a life that feels real, hyper real, one authentic choice at a time.</p>
      <p>The questions haven't stopped coming, but now they're welcomed companions rather than midnight tormentors. Each one is a chance to dig deeper, to grow stronger, to love fuller, starting with themselves.</p>
    </div>

